description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol is fighting for his political life after his attempt to break an impasse in parliament by briefly imposing martial law backfired. The incident was part of a series of blunders that has eroded public support and could lead to his impeachment.
title: Why a Dior Handbag Caused Such a Stir in South Korean Politics

description: Lyft Inc. is asking its customers in Chicago to urge the city’s council to reject a proposed tax on rideshares in the downtown zone during the weekend, marking the latest hurdle as Mayor Brandon Johnson races to close a nearly $1 billion deficit by year-end.
title: Lyft Urges Chicago Riders to Push City Council to Reject New Tax

description: Base salaries for regular workers in Japan rose by a record, a further indication of progress toward a positive economic cycle that will support market speculation of a near-term rate hike by the central bank.
title: Japan Base Pay Gains by Record, Keeps Door Open for BOJ Hike

description: As the city contends with a falling birth rate, the limits of reproductive assistance are causing strains.
title: Hong Kong’s IVF Rules Send People Into Black Market for Eggs, Embryos

description: This is Washington Edition, the newsletter about money, power and politics in the nation’s capital. Today, senior editor Joe Sobczyk looks at the continued uncertainty about Pete Hegseth’s nomination as Defense secretary. Sign up here and follow us at @bpolitics. Email our editors here.
title: Hegseth Drama Overshadows Musk and Ramaswamy at Capitol

description: Boston Mayor Michelle Wu’s plan to temporarily increase commercial property taxes has stalled again after new data indicated the impact from slumping office building values on the city’s tax system won’t be as stark as initially estimated.
title: Boston Mayor’s Plan to Raise Commercial Property Taxes Hits Snag

description: Emmanuel Macron said that he will serve out the remainder of his presidential term as he seeks to quickly stymie the political turmoil in France after Marine Le Pen’s far-right party allied with leftist lawmakers to topple his government.
title: French President Macron Vows to Serve Out Remainder of His Term

description: A key House Republican criticized the Biden administration’s latest attempt to curtail China’s chipmaking ambitions, saying US rules unveiled Monday leave loopholes that will let Chinese companies like Huawei Technologies Co. continue acquiring American technology.
title: GOP China Panel Chair Slams US Chip Curbs for Huawei ‘Loopholes’

description: Progressive governments in Latin America are doomed to fail unless they ensure macroeconomic stability, according to Colombia’s new finance minister.
title: Colombia’s New Finance Chief Says Leftists Fail When They Neglect Macro Stability

description: European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen shouldn’t be at the top of Emmanuel Macron’s list of problems these days.
title: Macron Resists EU Trade Deal as He Fights for Political Survival

description: Mali’s military-controlled government has issued an arrest warrant for money laundering against Barrick Gold Corp. Chief Executive Officer Mark Bristow amid an escalating dispute over mine revenues in the West African nation.
title: Mali Issues Arrest Warrant for Barrick Gold CEO Mark Bristow

description: Senate Republican Joni Ernst, a combat veteran and rape survivor influential with GOP colleagues on military matters, pointedly declined to support Pete Hegseth’s embattled defense secretary nomination, calling for further investigation of allegations against him.
title: GOP Senator Ernst Declines to Support Hegseth, Leaving Embattled Nominee in Limbo

description: Canada can expect to collect about C$100 million ($71.4 million) annually from its new tariffs on Chinese steel, aluminum and electric vehicles, Parliamentary Budget Officer Yves Giroux said in a report Thursday.
title: Canada to See Small Revenue Bump from China Tariffs, Report Says

description: Estonian authorities accused one of Russia’s spy agencies of organizing acts of vandalism, including smashing the interior minister’s car windows last year.
title: Estonia Says Russian Spy Agency Behind String of Vandalism Cases

description: The expansion of Canada’s Trans Mountain pipeline represented a $24 billion bid to help the country’s oil producers reduce their near-total reliance on the US market. That’s a bet that may pay off sooner than expected if President-elect Donald Trump follows through on his tariff threats.
title: Oil Patch in Canada Has $24 Billion Shield Against Trump Tariffs

description: Russia ordered the closure of Poland’s consulate in St. Petersburg and told three diplomats to leave the country as part of an escalating diplomatic confrontation.
title: Russia Closes Polish Consulate in Escalating Diplomatic Spat

description: Marine Le Pen said France can overcome government collapse to deliver a budget in “a matter of weeks” — so long as the next prime minister is prepared to narrow the deficit more slowly.
title: Le Pen Sees French Budget Within Weeks If Macron Eases Debt Path

description: The European Union’s defense chief floated a new joint borrowing mechanism for military spending as part of the bloc’s plan to seek some €500 billion ($527 billion) for security over the next decade.
title: EU Defense Chief Floats Joint Debt Funding Based on NATO Target

description: The conservative party of embattled South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol faces a quandary: How do members distance themselves from an unpopular leader without handing a big win to their political opponents.
title: South Korea’s Reviled Leader Is Likely to Survive Impeachment

description: The European Union should guard against Chinese attempts to dominate the bloc’s clean-tech market and make sure its exports aren’t destroying local rivals, the bloc’s new competition chief warned.
title: EU’s Ribera Vows Action Against China’s Clean Tech Dominance

description: Romania started an investigation into potential meddling in the first round of the presidential election that resulted in the surprise win of a little known pro-Russia candidate and triggered an unprecedented political crisis.
title: Romanian Prosecutors Start Probe Into Alleged Election Meddling

description: Keir Starmer pledged to fast-track the approval of at least 150 major infrastructure projects as one of a series of milestones he wants his new UK government to be measured by, as the prime minister tries to reset the political narrative after just five months in power.
title: Starmer Reset Bid Underscores UK Government’s Early Struggles

description: Syria’s army says it’s retreated from the city of Hama in the face of a rebel advance, according to the state news agency, dealing another blow to President Bashar al-Assad.
title: Syrian Army Says It’s Retreated From City of Hama: Sana

description: To Next Africa subscribers: We wanted to let you know about this newsletter, The Year of Elections, on the votes that matter to markets, business and policy amid the most fragmented geo-economic landscape in decades. We’re sharing this deep dive on Ghana’s election below.
title: Voters Look Set to Topple Another African Ruling Party

description: President-elect expected to exploit Democrat’s effort to tighten border amid campaign criticism.
title: Biden Clears Path for Trump’s Push to Crack Down on Immigration

description: French President Emmanuel Macron is looking to join forces with the Socialist party, a strategy that would split a large left-wing coalition in the National Assembly and potentially return enough power to centrists to be able to break the country’s political gridlock.
title: Macron Is Still Banking On Socialists to Break France’s Gridlock

description: Now that France’s lower house of parliament has toppled the government, plunging the country into further political turmoil, President Emmanuel Macron will need to try to get his agenda back on track.
title: Macron’s Top Choices to Become France’s Next Prime Minister

description: Welcome to Balance of Power, bringing you the latest in global politics. If you haven’t yet, sign up here.
title: Wounded Macron Needs a Notre-Dame-Like Revival

description: Ukraine’s top diplomat warned against the emergence of “gray zones” in which Russia could cement its influence as he reinforced Kyiv’s refusal to consider territorial concessions.
title: Ukraine’s Top Diplomat Rules Out Territorial Compromise

description: A majority of French people want Emmanuel Macron to resign and advance the presidential election scheduled for 2027 to next year, according to a poll by Cluster17 for Le Point magazine.
title: French Poll Shows Majority Want Presidential Election in 2025

description: European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen is set to arrive in Uruguay to attend the Mercosur summit as the bloc aims to conclude a long-sought trade deal with key Latin American nations.
title: EU Nears Deal With Mercosur as Von Der Leyen Heads to Summit

description: Elon Musk is heading to the Capitol on Thursday to stoke congressional enthusiasm for his ambitious effort to slash at least $2 trillion from the federal budget, a level of austerity unprecedented in the US since the winding down of World War II.
title: Elon Musk Works Congress as He Targets $2 Trillion Budget Chop

description: Will Notre Dame’s reopening be all that remains of Emmanuel Macron’s legacy?
title: Le Pen Takes France and Europe Into the Unknown

description: Producers of Cognac and Champagne are seeking to ship more bottles to the US as they brace for potential extra tariffs under President-elect Donald Trump.
title: Cognac and Champagne Makers Seek to Boost US Exports to Avoid Tariff Risks

description: South Korea’s main opposition leader said it might be difficult to garner enough support from the ruling party to impeach President Yoon Suk Yeol this week over his declaration of martial law.
title: South Korea Opposition Chief Says Ousting Yoon Will Be Difficult

description: South Korea’s opposition leader Lee Jae-myung, one of the leading contenders to replace the sitting president after a brief martial law decree, is in favor of bringing back the practice of short selling in the nation’s $1.6 trillion stock market.
title: South Korean Opposition Leader Lee Backs Return of Short Selling

description: A Malaysian Royal Commission of Inquiry has recommended that a police report be lodged against former Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad for his handling of a sovereignty dispute with Singapore over an island, according to a report made available on the parliament website.
title: Malaysia Royal Commission Recommends Probe Against Mahathir

description: Calin Georgescu's first-round election victory stunned a nation. Now he threatens to pivot one of the US's key allies in Europe toward Russia
title: The Tiktok-Loving Conspiracy Theorist Upending Romanian Politics

description: President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva’s proposal to tighten military retirement rules is facing opposition from part of the armed forces, potentially watering down an austerity plan that seeks to assuage investors worried about Brazil’s deteriorating finances.
title: Brazil’s Austerity Plan Faces Pushback From the Military

description: Hong Kong’s leader John Lee sacked his ministers for tourism and transport.
title: Hong Kong Leader Unexpectedly Sacks Tourism, Transport Ministers

description: The Philippines will file a diplomatic protest against Beijing following fresh encounters between Chinese and Philippine vessels in the disputed South China Sea.
title: Philippines to File Protest Against China After Sea Incidents

description: Chinese state media warned against blindly chasing faster growth and signaled more focus on boosting consumption in a flurry of articles setting the stage for a key economic meeting next week.
title: China Warns Against ‘Worship’ of Chasing Faster Economic Growth

description: US House Speaker Mike Johnson held a call with Taiwan President Lai Ching-te, Voice of America reported, a move likely to add to China’s reasons to step up military intimidation of the democracy.
title: US House Speaker Holds Call With Taiwan’s Leader, Report Says

description: Bank of Korea Governor Rhee Chang-yong expressed optimism that market volatility triggered by martial-law turmoil will gradually cool down barring new shocks. He continued his campaign to reassure investors who are casting doubts over South Korea’s economic outlook.
title: BOK’s Rhee Says Volatility Will Slowly Cool to Pre-Turmoil Level

description: Malaysian prosecutors charged the founders of a local online fashion retailer over the alleged misuse of funds invested in their company by two government-linked firms.
title: FashionValet Founders Charged After Sovereign Wealth Fund Loss

description: President-elect Donald Trump is nominating Frank Bisignano, the chief executive officer of fintech and payments company Fiserv Inc., to be the commissioner of the Social Security Administration.
title: Trump Taps Fiserv’s Bisignano for Social Security Administration

description: Today on the Big Take podcast: What lies ahead for France after President Macron's government collapsed in a historic vote.
title: After No-Confidence Vote, France Faces Tumult and Uncertainty

description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol named a new defense minister on Thursday after accepting the resignation of Kim Yong-hyun, following the opposition’s submission of motions to impeach both of them.
title: South Korea’s Yoon Replaces Defense Chief Amid Impeachment Move
